<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Specify Contours Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Specify Contours Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The Specify Contours dialog box is used to set the contour values, line thicknesses and colors of the contours. It is displayed by clicking the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Edit contours...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Contour_Data_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Contour Data</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Visualization_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Data Visualization</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Contour value</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> column of the table specifies the values for which contour lines will be drawn.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Line thickness</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> column specifies the width in pixels of those lines. Typically most lines are drawn with a thickness of two pixels and every fifth contour is drawn with a width of four pixels.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Contour color</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> column shows the color assigned to each contour. If the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Automatic colors</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> checkbox is not checked, the user can edit the colors. When the user selects a cell containing the color a button labeled Edit will appear. Clicking this button will display a dialog box in which the user can select a color. The user can also type a number representing the color in the cell. The numbers should be in hexadecimal notation. The first two digits represent the amount of blue in the color. The second two digits represent the amount of red in the color. The third two digit represent the amount of red in the color.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Number of rows</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> specifies the number of rows in the table of contour values.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Add row </text><image src="AddLayer.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Insert row </text><image src="InsertLayer.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Delete row </text><image src="DeleteLayer.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> buttons add a row to the end of the table, insert a row above the selected row, or delete the selected row from the table.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
